That sounds like a very intriguing and potentially meaningful encounter. Lets break this down to help you evaluate it rationally and maximize your chances of success while avoiding any risks.

1. First, Lets Talk About the Situation Itself

Its not every day someone offers you a 50-50 business partnership after meeting on a train. Here are a few things to reflect on:

  • Was this a genuine connection? Some people are highly intuitive or spiritual and might genuinely feel that meeting you was fate. That said, unusual generosity from strangers should always be handled with caution.

  • Why did she offer 50-50? A 50-50 partnership is a big deal. Normally, someone would only offer that if:

    • They need a skillset you have (like marketing).

    • They trust you deeply or are desperate to find a trustworthy partner.

    • Or, sometimes, they dont fully understand what theyre giving away.

2. Due Diligence on Dentelin.eu

Lets look at the business you might be partnering in:

  • What does Dentelin.eu do? (Is it active? Selling products/services? What's the revenue model?)

  • Who owns it? Can you verify she is the actual owner?

  • Is the domain active and the business legally registered?

  • How does the business make money? Is there an actual product-market fit?

I can look into this online for you if you'd like just confirm.

3. The Role of Advertising & Your Strengths

If shes expecting you to handle advertising, ask yourself:

  • Do you have experience in digital marketing, social media ads, SEO, content creation, or branding?

  • Do you have the budget, tools, and time to create and manage ad campaigns?

Advertising can grow a business dramatically, but only if:

  • The product is strong

  • The target market is clear

  • The advertising strategy is sound

  • You track ROI closely

Youll need to clarify what she expects from you and what she will contribute.

4. Business Agreement

Before doing anything:

  • Dont just shake hands. Get everything in writing.

  • Define:

    • Ownership structure

    • Profit/loss sharing

    • Responsibilities (who does what?)

    • What happens if one person wants out?

  • You might consider a basic contract or at least a Memorandum of Understanding (MOU).

5. Red Flags to Watch For

  • If she asks for money upfront pause and think.

  • If shes vague about the business details ask more questions.

  • If youre expected to do all the work and she just benefits reconsider.

  • If you feel rushed take a breath. No good deal disappears overnight.

Your Gut Feeling

Its okay to be excited. But excitement should be paired with due diligence. Many great business partnerships start from unexpected places but many scams or mismatched ventures do too.

How to Publish on GitHub Pages (Free)

  • Click "Add file" > "Upload files"

  • Upload the index.html file you downloaded

  • Commit the changes

Step 4: Enable GitHub Pages

  • Go to Settings of the repository

  • Scroll down to Pages

  • Under Source, choose "Deploy from a branch"

  • Choose branch: main, folder: / (root)

  • Click Save

TypeNameValue
A@185.199.108.153
A@185.199.109.153
A@185.199.110.153
A@185.199.111.153

CNAME Record (optional, for www.smilecation.com):

TypeNameValue
CNAMEwwwyourusername.github.io

  1. Then go back to GitHub and re-enter smilecation.com into the Custom Domain field and save.

DNS changes can take up to 24 hours, but usually start working in 12 hours.
